caption.text: This Independence Day, aside from raging nationalism and local festivities, let's not forget that Bhinneka Tunggal Ika is still an empty statement. Let's not forget the intolerance of other religions other than Islam, let's not forget the intolerance of other sexualities and gender identities besides cisheterosexuality, let's not forget the intolerance of other races even though they were born on Indonesian soil and are legally Indonesian citizens. Let's not forget Papuans (Melanesians). Let's not forget the hidden but present lgbtq community. Let's not forget that you still need to state one of the big five religions on your identity card even though you might have no religious affiliations or have one that is outside of the big five. Though it's now been 71 years since the "official" end of the Dutch occupation, we're still so far from achieving what the founders of this nation wrote down in the original constitution. #agustusanrant
